  "description": "Today&#8217;s podcast guest is Brigadier General Gary Stafford, OMM, CD. In 1970, Brigadier-General Stafford joined The Royal Regiment of Canada as a Private and progressed to the rank of Chief Warrant Officer in 1983. He held the position of Regimental Sergeant Major from 1983 to 1987. In 1988, Brigadier-General Stafford commissioned from the ranks, promoted to Captain and posted to Toronto Militia District Headquarters (now 32 Canadian Brigade Group) as the Recruiting Officer for one year. He returned to The [&#8230;]",
  "content:encoded": "<p>Today&#8217;s podcast guest is Brigadier General Gary Stafford, OMM, CD.</p>\n<p>In 1970, <a title=\"Brigadier-General Gary Stafford, OMM, CD\" href=\"http://www.theroyalregimentofcanada.org/?p=631\" target=\"_blank\">Brigadier-General Stafford</a> joined <a title=\"The Royal Regiment of Canada\" href=\"http://www.theroyalregimentofcanada.org/\" target=\"_blank\">The Royal Regiment of Canada</a> as a Private and progressed to the rank of Chief Warrant Officer in 1983. He held the position of Regimental Sergeant Major from 1983 to 1987.</p>\n<p>In 1988, Brigadier-General Stafford commissioned from the ranks, promoted to Captain and posted to Toronto Militia District Headquarters (now <a title=\"32 Canadian Brigade Group\" href=\"http://www.army-armee.forces.gc.ca/en/32-cbg/index.page\" target=\"_blank\">32 Canadian Brigade Group</a>) as the Recruiting Officer for one year. He returned to The Royal Regiment of Canada where, in 1992, he was promoted to Major.</p>\n<p>In 1999, he was promoted Lieutenant-Colonel and appointed Commanding Officer of The Royal Regiment of Canada.  Gary Stafford went on to command 32 Canadian Brigade Group before deploying to <a title=\"Op Athena\" href=\"http://www.forces.gc.ca/en/operations-abroad-past/op-athena.page\" target=\"_blank\">Afghanistan</a> in 2006.  Upon his return, he was promoted to the rank of Brigadier General and was appointed as the Deputy Commander of Land Force Central Area, which is now known as the <a title=\"4th Canadian Division\" href=\"http://www.army-armee.forces.gc.ca/en/central/index.page\" target=\"_blank\">4th Canadian Division</a>.  He retired from the <a title=\"Canadian Armed Forces\" href=\"http://www.forces.gc.ca/en/index.page\" target=\"_blank\">Canadian Armed Forces </a>as the Deputy Commander of Land Force Doctrine and Training System (now the <a title=\"Doctrine and Training\" href=\"http://www.army.gc.ca/en/doctrine-training/index.page?\" target=\"_blank\">Canadian Army Doctrine and Training Centre</a>) in 2010.</p>\n<p>As a reservist, he had a second career as a police officer with the <a title=\"Toronto Police Service\" href=\"http://www.torontopolice.on.ca/\" target=\"_blank\">Toronto Police Service</a> where he attained the rank of Staff Sergeant.</p>\n<p>Follow me on Twitter @MikeLacroix32 and keep track of my results on #Mike100Workouts</p>\n<p>You can support this site by shopping on <a title=\"Amazon.ca\" href=\"http://www.amazon.ca?_encoding=UTF8&tag=thecanamilihi-20\" target=\"_blank\">Amazon</a>.  You still enjoy Amazon&#8217;s great prices, but a portion of your purchase goes to supporting the show.</p>\n<audio class=\"wp-audio-shortcode\" id=\"audio-423-47\" preload=\"none\" style=\"width: 100%;\" controls=\"controls\"><source type=\"audio/mpeg\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CMHP-Episode-018-BGen-Gary-Stafford.mp3?_=47\" /><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CMHP-Episode-018-BGen-Gary-Stafford.mp3\">http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/CMHP-Episode-018-BGen-Gary-Stafford.mp3</a></audio>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Cadet.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-426\" alt=\"Gary Cadet\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Cadet-212x300.jpg\" width=\"212\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Cadet-212x300.jpg 212w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Cadet-726x1024.jpg 726w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Cadet.jpg 1472w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 212px) 100vw, 212px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Young Private Gary Stafford of the Royal Regiment of Canada in 1970.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Scarlet-Uniform.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-427\" alt=\"Gary Scarlet Uniform\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Scarlet-Uniform-237x300.jpg\" width=\"237\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Scarlet-Uniform-237x300.jpg 237w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Scarlet-Uniform-811x1024.jpg 811w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Gary-Scarlet-Uniform.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 237px) 100vw, 237px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Warrant Officer Gary Stafford at the archway next to Fort York Armoury.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCF0096.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-424\" alt=\"DSCF0096\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCF0096-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCF0096-300x225.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCF0096-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCF0096.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Col Gary Stafford, Commander 32 Canadian Brigade Group, in Toronto.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Afgan-06.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"Afgan 06\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Afgan-06-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a></p>\n<p>Col Stafford mentoring the Afghan National Police in 2006.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCN0142.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-425\" alt=\"DSCN0142\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCN0142-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCN0142-300x225.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCN0142-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/DSCN0142.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Col Gary Stafford and BGen Greg Young &#8211; Both former commanders of 32 Canadian Brigade Group.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Back-from-Patrol.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-429\" alt=\"Back from Patrol\" src=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Back-from-Patrol-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Back-from-Patrol-300x225.jpg 300w, http://podcast.canadianmilitaryhistorypodcast.ca/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Back-from-Patrol.jpg 640w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Col Stafford back from patrol.</p>\n",
